  -> seams:1 resolved:1 flagged:0 | max drop PER SIDE: prev 6tok curr 4tok (per-side cap 8; both within)

[concat(jfk+harvard+washington)] 5 segs, assembled 300w, assembled-loop: none
  seam seg0->seg1 | exact_overlap_trim | drop-curr 1tok "Well,"
  seam seg1->seg2 | exact_overlap_trim | drop-curr 3tok "a smooth road,"
  seam seg2->seg3 | exact_overlap_trim | drop-curr 3tok "an immutable decision,"
  seam seg3->seg4 | exact_overlap_trim | drop-curr 3tok "his own deficiencies."
  -> seams:4 resolved:4 flagged:0 | max drop PER SIDE: prev 0tok curr 3tok (per-side cap 8; both within)

PATH-3 liveness (no-anchor seam -> keep-both+flag): PASS (trimPrev=0, kept=4/4, reason=NO_BOUNDED_MATCH__kept_both__FLAG)

Policy: (1) exact bounded overlap trim (<=6tok); (2) bounded FUZZY anchor splice within the overlap window (anchor=longest common run >=2; drop prev-tail-after + curr-head-before, per-side cap 8); (3) else keep-both+FLAG. No global de-dup, no out-of-window trim, never silent deletion of UNIQUE speech (each dropped span is overlap audio the other segment still covers; WER reaching the content floor confirms no real loss).
